.13039/100001448", "id-type": "DOI", "asserted-by": "publisher"}]}], "content-domain": {"domain": ["journals.asm.org"], "crossmark-restriction": true}, "short-container-title": ["mBio"], "published-print": {"date-parts": [[2025, 8, 13]]}, "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title><jats:sec><jats:title/><jats:p>Many difficult-to-understand clinical features characterize COVID-19 and post-acute sequelae of COVID-19 (PASC or long COVID [LC]). The SARS-CoV-2 Spike protein receptor-binding domain (RBD) binds angiotensin converting enzyme 2 (ACE2) on the surface of host cells to initiate infection.</jats:p></jats:sec><jats:sec><jats:title>IMPORTANCE</jats:title><jats:p>Patients who have had COVID-19 can sometimes have troublesome symptoms, termed post-acute sequelae of COVID-19 (PASC) or long COVID (LC). We show that patients convalescing from COVID-19 also make antibodies that act like ACE2.</jats:p></jats:sec>", "DOI": "10.1128/mbio.01735-25", "type": "journal-article", "created": {"date-parts": [[2025, 7, 22]], "date-time": "2025-07-22T00:00:00Z", "timestamp": 1753142400000}, "source": "Crossref", "is-referenced-by-count": 0, "title": ["ACE-2-like enzymatic activity in COVID-19 convalescents with persistent pulmonary symptoms associated with immunoglobulin"], "prefix": "10.1128", "volume": "16", "author": [{"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0009-0001-6788-1717", "authenticated-orcid": false, "given": "Yufeng", "family": "Song", "sequence": "first", "affiliation": [{"id": [{"id": "https://ror.org/0153tk833", "id-type": "ROR", "asserted-by": "publisher"}], "name": "Department of Pediatrics, University of Virginia", "place": ["Charlottesville, USA"]}]}, {"ORCID": "https://orcid.org/0009-0005-9929-3185", "authenticated-orcid": false, "given": "Frances", "family": "Mehl", "sequence": "additional", "affiliation": [{"id": [{"id": "https://ror.org/0153tk833", "id-type": "ROR", "asserted-by": "publisher"}], "name": "Department of Pediatrics, University of Virginia", "place": ["Ch